title: For Sale:  FNH Husqvarna Browning 1907 in .380
postcontent:
If you are thinking that this looks like a Colt 1903 longslide (which was never made) you are right! Sort of... What we have here is a Fabrique Nationale d'Herstal Browning 1903 pattern modified to the specifications of the Swedish military for adoption in 1907 as their primary service pistol as the M1907. These guns were made by FN and imported to Sweden until the FN factory was captured by Germans during the Great War. After that Husqvarna began production and eventually produced them for Columbia and other countries after the end of WW1.

This great little gun served with distinction up until the adoption of the Lahti in the 1940's. Once out of field use, they were still preferred by police and officers due to their compact dimensions and great handling. They were also used by several European, Middle Eastern and South American countries as well as the Russian and Ottoman Empires! If you like unusual guns with a storied history, this one is for you.

This gun is in great shape considering its age. Finish is very good at around 92-95%, bore is good and still shoots great. These are hugely overbuilt by todays standards for .380 so I would have no worries shooting +p or defensive ammo out of it. Best of all, you are probably the only person at the range with one! Needless to say these don't pop up every day so don't let this one pass you by.

F2F within about an hour of Charlottesville. No lowballers or tire kickers please. Take a look at my other listings for more fun toys.

title: For Sale:  Buffalo Bore Ammo - .32 ACP +P Ammo - 75 gr. Hardcast F.N. (1150fps/ M.E. 220 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
https://www.extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=132

.32 ACP +P Ammo - 75 gr. Hardcast F.N. (1150fps/ M.E. 220 ft. lbs.) - 20 Round Box

The 32 ACP auto inhabits a valuable and useful place in our society as a defensive cartridge, mostly because of the easily concealable, tiny pistols chambered for it. HOWEVER, because of the very limited size of the cartridge, it is plagued with limited power and therefore most of the existing ammo in 32 ACP suffers from not being reliable as a man-stopper. We've studied and examined nearly all available 32 ammo and find it wanting as a reliable means of self defense, especially against a large, drugged up/pain free, determined attacker.

Here's the problem. The current 32 ACP frangible ammo delivers a large amount of surface trauma, but lacks sufficient penetration. For example, if you shot me or another sane man in the face, with modern, frangible 32 ACP ammo, it would blow off a big portion of my cheek. I would undoubtedly fall to the ground in shock and pain, but I would be very much alive and functional if I could get past the pain, as that frangible bullet would have stopped somewhere in my face, never making it to my brain. However, if you shot a drugged up maniac in the face with that same frangible bullet and blew half his cheek off, he would keep right on coming because he is insane and is not thinking like you or I. Plus, he is likely pain free and fear free and won't know that part of his cheek is missing and if he did know, he would not care. So, whatever 32 ACP ammo you shoot him in the face with, had better go through his face and blow his brain stem out the back of his head, because only a CNS (central nervous system) hit with a 32 ACP is going to stop him. Likewise, a torso hit to the sternum needs to penetrate deep enough to blow all the way through his spine in order to shut him down instantly. If you fail to shut him down instantly, you and your loved ones are going to have to find a way to survive while you wait for him to bleed out and pass out. The best chance of survival for you and your loved ones, is to shut down the attacker instantly. So, we've designed this 32 ACP+P load to keep you and yours alive under the worst of scenarios.

This 32 ACP+P ammo will better all American made 32 ACP+P ammo by 110 fps to 150 fps with a heavier bullet than any other American made 32 ACP ammo.

Item 30A/20 is a 75gr. HARD cast bullet with a flat nose. It is traveling over 1,000 fps out of my 3.4 inch Beretta Mod. 70. We've used a flash suppressed powder so that you won't be blinded by your own gunfire in the dark. This is significant as well over 90% of all civilian shootings in America occur in low light when the criminal element is out and about. Also, this flat nosed, nonexpanding, hard cast, bullet will penetrate deeply and will do much more damage than the typical round nosed FMJ bullet. Round nosed bullets tend to slip and slide through living tissue, doing little damage as opposed to a flat nosed bullet. The flat nose not only wounds much more than a round nosed bullet, but it actually keeps the penetration straight and thus deeper. Notice the below velocities from my personal 32 ACP pistols. These are real world guns and thus the speeds are realistic and not the exaggerated speeds you'll see produced from laboratory test barrels. What you see with Buffalo Bore Ammo advertising, is truly what you get in the "real world" where it matters. You can expect 20+ inches of straight line penetration in flesh and bone with this load. If you are worried about over-penetration with this load, DON'T! You chose to carry a tiny under-powered 32 ACP pistol and the trade off is that now you are going to have to stay alive using this pistol and over-penetration will be the least of your worries if you end up needing this gun to save yourself or your family.

A. Berretta Mod. 70, 3 inch bbl.- 1001 fps

B. Kel Tek, 2.5 inch bbl - 910 fps

C. Seecamp, 2 inch bbl. - 856 fps

The above bullet speeds are 110 fps to 150 fps faster than the Winchester 71 gr. FMJ ammo on the American market. Not only is our bullet heavier than any other American made 32 ACP ammo, but it is moving about 15% to 20% faster - with that heavier bullet!
Feeding and function was flawless in the three test pistols listed above.

title: For Sale:  shtf, fire starting supplies, survival fire source, ferrocerium rods, magnesium, etc
postcontent:
I inherited this project from a family member that abonded it and I just never had the time to do anything with it. 

Everything pictured is included, there's quite a bit of fatwood, fatwood shavings, dust, etc. Magnesium shavings, rods, etc. Ferocerium fire steels in various sizes, easily over a hundred rods. And half as many magnesium rods, squares, etc.The idea at the time was to create little fire starting kits to give out / sell at various events, keep some for preps, etc. 

There are 10 + rolls of jute cord, some frayed, petroleum jelly and wax to coat it. For anyone who's made their own accelerants, these will make sense. In places where it's sometimes difficult to find dry tinder (the NW) having premade accelerants greatly increases your chance of success with fire, and they burn longer than tinder would. 

All of the Pre prepared magnesium, fatwood shavings, dust, etc is stored in sealed tins or plastic containers in preparation. The idea was to include some of each in fire starting kits.

Some of what is included was at various stages of completion as you can see from the pictures and while I know the cost of everything it's incredibly difficult to price.

I prefer trades, open to offers of hunting, fishing, outdoors gear, ammo in .40, other survival, knives, prep oriented gear, etc. It would be perfect  for a scout troop as a project, or prep group. If i cant find a trade and anyone has a troop in mind I'll likely just donate it.

Thanks

I present to you the Daniel Defense DDM4 V5 M4 Carbine Mil-Spec Rifle. Below is a link giving the specifics of this same rifle for sale (except the stock). I purchased and added on to this rifle after doing many months of research on creating the "perfect weapon system" for any defensive/offensive situation in virtually any scenario that would come up. ONLY reason I am selling is because I am saving up for a full auto, so my baby has to go...

As part of building this weapon system, I chose the:

-Daniel Defense M4 Carbine because it kept popping up in list after list of the "best of the best" because of its durability, attention to detail/quality, and adherence to Military Specifications/tolerances. Watch this video on YouTube and you'll see why the DDM4 is the best M4/AR15 on the market from a durability standpoint http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y1kX0nCEh5E

-Burris MTAC Ballistic CQ/LR (Close Quarter/Long Range) tactical optic because it offers both Close Quarters and Medium/Long Range capabilities in the same platform and the same time. Using "true 1x" it allows for both eyes open use (just like a red dot...AimPoint for example), and up to 4x magnification with built in 5.56 BDC reticles for effective engagements up to 600 yards. Just zero for 100 yards (which it already is) and your ready to go out to 600 yards using the built in BDC dots. It is extremely clear, has illuminated reticle (which work even if the battery dies), weather and shock proof, with a lifetime warranty. It is just like having both a Red Dot and a Tactical magnified scope in one, giving you the best of both worlds in one small, lightweight package.

-5.11 LED Tactical Lightweight High Output Weapons light because of it's superior performance inside of an extremely light frame. It is weather/shock proof with high, low, and strobe capabilities. Mounts perfect along side the foregrip for easy of use in any conditions.

-45 degree backup sight for obvious reasons; just in case something were to happen the MTAC optic this rifle can still be effective at close and medium/long ranges.
